        "difficultyTier": "intermediate",
        "hiddenInfo": "While the Underdock operates as a gray economy serving those the surface world rejects, tensions are reaching a breaking point. Pirha Nimeryu, the phase-touched catkin whose condition makes her lethal to normal people, has been wandering the district desperately seeking helpher stabilizer supply is running out, and each uncontrolled phase causes excruciating pain while spreading cellular dissolution to anyone she accidentally touches. Most Underdock denizens avoid her out of fear, though Tourniquet has provided temporary treatments in exchange for allowing him to study her unique condition, his disturbing fascination with her suffering masked as medical curiosity. Meanwhile, surface nobles have grown tired of the Underdock's existence beneath their respectable port city, viewing it as a stain on Port Lume's reputation and a haven for criminals who undermine legitimate commerce. They have quietly assembled a coalition of merchant houses and hired mercenaries, planning a coordinated strike to 'cleanse' the districtburning out the fighting pits, arresting or killing everyone present, and sealing the entrances permanently. Rumors of the impending attack circulate through dockside taverns and warehouse gossip, with nervous workers whispering about increased mercenary recruitment and nobles stockpiling weapons, though most Underdock residents dismiss the warnings as paranoia until it's too late. The assault is planned for the new moon in two weeks, when darkness will provide cover and Luna's faithful will be at their weakesta calculated cruelty that reveals how thoroughly the nobles have planned their purge.",
