        "difficultyTier": "intermediate",
        "hiddenInfo": "Clan Stormwake's prosperity depends on a relationship they don't fully understand. Before each whaling season, the clan elder makes offerings at a specific point in the bay whale oil, carved bones, songs sung in an ancient language no one remembers learning. The tradition is older than the clan itself, inherited from whoever lived here before. Deep beneath the bay lives a community of ancient, intelligent beings not demons, not fey, but something else entirely. They're survivors of a civilization that predates even the Lunarians, beings who chose to retreat beneath the waters rather than interact with surface peoples. The offerings are a form of communication: we respect your territory, please continue allowing us to hunt. The clan elder's granddaughter, Ketra Stormwake, secretly followed her grandmother during the last offering ritual and saw something rise from the depths to receive it. She's become obsessed with making contact, believing these beings possess knowledge that could help Frostrend survive the changing climate. Her attempts at independent contact have been noticed by the deep dwellers, who are disturbed by the breach of protocol. They're debating whether to continue tolerating the whalers or drive them away permanently. A whale Ketra was tracking has gone missing in the deep waters, and her search may force a confrontation that determines whether the ancient arrangement survives.Player may be approached by Ketra and ask for help she did not receive from her village",
