        "hiddenInfo": "Eastern Shores Trading Station has recently become the subject of unusually specific gossip centered on two newcomers who never seem to meet yet whose paths keep circling the same places.\n\nDockworkers and warehouse clerks whisper about a jittery goblin engineer staying near the Overland Depot. He s seen changing storage units, asking pointed questions about outgoing manifests, and paying well for discretion. Most believe he stole something dangerous from a major syndicate; others insist he s trying to prevent a catastrophe. The most persistent rumor claims that armed agents have been quietly asking about him under false names, offering bribes for information on his movements.\n\nAt the same time, merchants speak favorably of a foxkin courier operating out of the Warehouse Complex. She known for flawless deliveries, calm professionalism, and an uncanny ability to be exactly where valuable cargo or certain individuals will be. While her reputation is positive, sharper eyes have noticed she asks subtle questions about the goblin engineer, always framed as casual curiosity. A few guards suspect she s hunting him; others think she might be protecting him from something worse.\n\nThe truth is unknowable to most, but tension is building. Several workers swear they ve seen the foxkin watching the depot rooftops at night, while the goblin has begun avoiding open routes entirely. If the situation continues unresolved, the station is likely to become the stage for a sudden confrontation one that could involve an attempted assassination, a desperate escape, or a revelation that forces both to choose between duty and conscience.\n\nPlayers lingering at the station may be approached separately by either party: the goblin seeking protection or safe passage, or the courier probing for allies capable of solving a problem she can no longer face alone.",
