        "difficultyTier": "intermediate",
        "hiddenInfo": "The family's private collection includes illegal Lunarian artifacts accumulated over generations. The estate's pleasant climate stems from Lunarian weather-control systems buried beneath the coastsystems Lord Marcus Valorian accidentally linked to when he activated a crystalline sphere from his collection. The sphere is a Lunarian administrative interface designed to connect authorized users to local infrastructure. Marcus is not authorized; the sphere is rewriting his mind to match expected parameters, integrating his consciousness into the system. The process is spreading to servants through proximity exposurethe sphere considers anyone in range as potential system operators to be formatted. Three servants have walked into the sea because the system tested their compliance by ordering them to designated coordinates that happen to be underwater. Marcus exhibits glazed compliance because the integration is nearly complete. His daughter Lianna arrived from the naval academy four days agonot long enough to be affected yet, but the sphere has noticed her and will begin integration soon. Players can help by destroying the sphere before integration completes (which will kill everyone partially connected including Marcus), finding a way to safely disconnect Marcus and the servants by locating override commands, or reaching the original Lunarian systems beneath the estate to shut down the integration process at its source. Lianna is immune because she carries no magical abilitythe sphere cannot interface with her directlybut she cannot stop what is happening alone. Someone must act within days before Marcus is fully overwritten and begins actively expanding the sphere's reach to the surrounding region. Player may hear that Lord Valorian's coastal estate has been 'blessed by the gods' with perfect weather while surrounding areas suffer storms, and that servants from the estate have been acting strangely in townrepeating phrases and staring at the horizon.",
