        "hiddenInfo": "Competing spy networks have turned the customs station into a battlefield. The Aurelion network is run by Senior Inspector Mira Coinsworth, who uses her position to identify valuable cargo, track merchant movements, and occasionally lose paperwork for ships carrying Silent Ledger interests. Her agents are embedded among porters and dock workers. The Lumeris operation is coordinated by a merchant named Aldous Fairweather, whose trading company is a front for Republican intelligence. He's particularly interested in weapons shipments, Zerathis troop movements, and any technology transfers that might shift the continental balance. Both networks recently tried to recruit the same asset a young customs clerk named Pella who has photographic memory and access to all cargo manifests. She accepted both offers, playing them against each other for maximum profit. Now both networks suspect betrayal but aren't sure who betrayed whom. A Zerathis merchant ship carrying undeclared military magitech is due to arrive in three days. Both Aurelion and Lumeris want to seize it but the cargo is actually a deliberate plant by House Serakai, designed to identify which customs officials are compromised. Whoever moves on the cargo exposes their entire network. Players in this location may be approached by either party to help them achieve their goals.",
