        "difficultyTier": "intermediate",
        "hiddenInfo": "The lodge exists because of an ancient bargain with the fey that is rapidly breaking down. Centuries ago, settlers made a deal with the Thornwood Court, a fey community led by a being called the Verdant Duchess humans could harvest timber and hunt game, but only in marked zones, only during certain seasons, and only after leaving specific offerings at designated stones. The traditions survived but their meaning was forgotten. Lodge Master Aldric Greenhollow has been pressured by an Aurelion logging consortium to increase harvest. He needs the money desperately because his daughter is sick and requires expensive treatment in Aurelion. He has reluctantly expanded into forbidden zones, stopped making offerings which he dismisses as peasant superstition, and begun clear-cutting rather than selective harvesting. The fey response has escalated from small violations like tools going missing and food spoiling overnight to terrifying retaliationloggers experiencing hallucinations, one man found wandering naked and aged forty years overnight, another who won't stop laughing. The Verdant Duchess has sent her herald,  Whisperthorn, to deliver a final warning: honor the compact in thirty days or the forest will reclaim everything. Making matters worse, the logging consortium has hired mercenaries to deal with the wildlife problem. If they kill fey creatures, the compact shatters entirely and Rimewood becomes actively hostile to all mortals. The rangers know something is terribly wrong but don't understand the true cause.",
