        "difficultyTier": "intermediate",
        "hiddenInfo": "The market's carefully maintained neutrality is threatened by murder. Ambassador Lorenz Greyfallow, an unofficial Aurelion envoy who conducted back-channel negotiations with imperial interests, was found dead in his quarters poisoned. His death threatens to collapse diplomatic contacts that have prevented three border incidents from becoming wars. Multiple parties had motive: Zerathis hardliners who opposed negotiation, Aurelion merchants who profited from tension, a scorned lover from the imperial side, a rival diplomat seeking his position, and someone unexpected the ambassador's own daughter Mira, who discovered he'd been selling out Aurelion interests to enrich himself. Both Aurelion and Zerathis want the murder quietly resolved without public investigation a trial would expose the back-channel diplomacy and embarrass everyone. But the market's independent arbiters demand justice, and the merchant families won't accept a murderer operating with impunity. The real killer is actually a Convergence Industrial Syndicate agent eliminating Greyfallow because his negotiations would have opened imperial markets to competition, threatening Syndicate monopolies. The Syndicate has planted evidence implicating an imperial merchant named Dorian Ashford, hoping to reignite tensions and protect their business interests. Dorian is currently under house arrest, protesting his innocence, scheduled for execution in five days unless the real killer is found. Players here may hear gossips about arrest that might suggest that Dorian is innocent.",
