        "difficultyTier": "beginner",
        "hiddenInfo": "The estate's manager, a high goblin named Trix Ledgerbound, has discovered discrepancies in the property records suggesting the estate's borders were deliberately redrawn fifty years ago to exclude a section of land. Investigation revealed an abandoned building in the excluded area containing records of a failed experiment: Council of Seats-funded research into magical crop enhancement that produced horrifying resultsvegetables that screamed when harvested, grain that caused prophetic nightmares, and fruit that granted temporary telepathy followed by permanent madness. The research was classified and the land legally separated from the estate to hide the Council's involvement. Trix has been quietly selling information about this to multiple parties: the Veiled Archive wants the research notes, House Hadrick wants leverage over the Council, and a mysterious buyer wants the actual seeds, which may still be viable in the sealed cold storage beneath the ruined facility. The competing interests are converging, and Trix is playing them against each other for maximum profit, unaware that one of the buyers is actually a Noctyra cultist seeking the madness-fruit for ritual purposes. Player may hear that the estate is experiencing unusual livestock behavior, with animals refusing to graze near the estate's western boundary and becoming agitated during certain moon phases",
