        "difficultyTier": "intermediate",
        "hiddenInfo": "The border between civilization and wilderness is shifting in ways the Republic doesn't understand. Three communities within the station's patrol area maintain hidden Virex shrines, continuing traditions that predate the Republic. The worship isn't political resistance these are people who believe the wild god protects them from the dangers beyond the border. Station Commander Helena Vrost knows and looks the other way, seeing no harm in peasant superstitions. Over the past year, rangers have documented increasingly strange phenomena: animals behaving with unusual coordination, plants growing in patterns that seem deliberate, weather that targets specific locations. Veteran Ranger Cassian Thornhill believes the forest itself is becoming more aware, more active but his reports are dismissed as stress-induced imagination. What the rangers are actually witnessing is a fey community relocating from deeper wilderness, driven out by something worse. The fey are testing whether they can coexist with the border settlements, sending scouts, observing human behavior, and making small interventions to see how people react. What drove the fey from their original territory is a corrupted nature spirit a fragment of Virex's power that became isolated and twisted during some long-ago magical catastrophe. It's slowly expanding its territory, converting normal wilderness into something predatory. The fey are refugees; soon, the border communities will face the same threat.",
