        "difficultyTier": "intermediate",
        "hiddenInfo": "The lighthouse keeper's family has maintained a secret for twelve generations: they are oath-bound guardians of a sea cave beneath the cliffs that contains the preserved body of a Luna paladin who sacrificed herself three centuries ago to seal something in the depths below. The seal requires renewal every lunar cycle through a specific ritual the family has performed without failuntil last month, when the current keeper's daughter eloped with a sailor, breaking the family line of succession. The keeper, an elderly man named Leon Waveborn, is dying of a wasting illness and desperately seeking someone worthy to inherit the duty. The seal has begun weakening; fishermen report seeing lights in the waters below the cliffs and hearing singing that compels them toward the rocks. The local fishing village has lost three boats in the past month to 'navigation errors' that drove them onto the cliffs at night. Sealed below is demon that feeds on drowning people and it's awakening, and Leon fears he won't live long enough to find a successor. The Lunar Concordance has no records of this paladin or her sacrifice, suggesting the oath predates modern religious organization. Player may hear that the lighthouse has been signaling in an archaic emergency code that no living person should know, and that Leon Waveborn is offering his family's entire savings to anyone who can locate his estranged daughter",
