        "difficultyTier": "intermediate",
        "hiddenInfo": "Volcanic activity has increased because deep extraction has disturbed Lunarian geothermal management systemsthe precursors built facilities here to tap volcanic energy and needed sophisticated controls to prevent eruptions. Mining has damaged those controls, and tremors grow worse each week. Miners broke into a chamber containing a dormant portal frame that the Lunarians used for rapid transportation between distant facilities. The Sunbound Continuum team investigating the discovery has detected movement on the other side of the inactive portalsomething is trying to come through from wherever the portal once connected. The portal links to another Lunarian facility that was overrun during the Quietus War; what moves on the other side is a Quietus remnant that has been waiting for millennia for the portal to reactivate. The Continuum wants to activate the portal to study what's there, not understanding the danger. The mining company wants the chamber cleared regardless of consequences. Foreman Gresham Coalhand has realized he helped uncover something that will kill everyone if the portal opens, and he wants it sealed permanently. Players can investigate the portal to confirm what waits on the other side, help Gresham sabotage the Continuum's activation attempts, find ways to stabilize the damaged geothermal systems before volcanic activity buries the decision under lava, or seal the chamber permanently with the Quietus remnant trapped. The Continuum's lead researcher, Dr. Helena Vex, is not evilshe simply does not believe the danger is real and needs convincing evidence. Player may hear that mining operations have been mysteriously delayed in a specific sector, that imperial officials have been visiting more frequently than usual, and that old Gresham has been telling anyone who'll listen to 'stay away from shaft seven.",
