        "difficultyTier": "intermediate",
        "hiddenInfo": "The seasonal trade routes serve as conduits for information and sensitive cargo because they are difficult to monitor and cross multiple jurisdictions. This season, three intelligence networks have converged on Frostrend hunter Ragnar Iceblood, who discovered a Lunarian cache in the deep ice and has been selling artifacts to fund treatment for his daughter Anja's wasting sickness. Republican agent Celeste Fairwind wants the cache location to secure precursor technology for Lumeris. Frost Covenant operative Brother Varn wants it for religious and research purposes. A Sunbound Continuum agent named Darius Coldwell arrived yesterday with orders to extract the location by any means necessaryincluding eliminating Ragnar after he talks. Ragnar senses something wrong with the intense interest but does not understand the danger. He wants to save his daughter and return to hunting. The cache contains a Lunarian emergency shelter with preserved supplies and equipment. The trading season ends in three weeks; after that, Ragnar disappears into territory where outsiders cannot follow, taking the cache's location with him. Players can protect Ragnar from the Continuum agent, help him negotiate safely with one of the factions, accompany him to the cache to properly assess and secure its contents, or claim the cache themselves. Celeste Fairwind is the most trustworthy of the agents and will deal fairly if given the chance. Brother Varn serves the Covenant's agenda above Ragnar's interests. Darius Coldwell will kill anyone who interferes with his mission. Player may hear that a hunter named Ragnar has been showing off strange southern-looking trinkets that 'came from the ice,' that two merchants have been competing aggressively for his attention, and that a third party from even further south has been asking questions about Lunarian artifacts.",
