        "difficultyTier": "beginner",
        "hiddenInfo": "The infamous privateer captain 'Iron' Jorgen Blackwater retired to this remote settlement fifteen years ago after making his fortune raiding Zerathis merchant shipping during the last trade war. He's lived quietly as a fisherman, but his past has finally caught up with him. Three parties have converged on the settlement simultaneously: Tio Varnhollow, daughter of a merchant house Jorgen ruined, seeking legal restitution; 'Scarred' Thomlin, a former crewmate who claims Jorgen cheated the crew out of their shares from a legendary prize called the Amber Hoard; and a young Zerathis naval officer investigating war crimes. Each wants something different justice, money, or Jorgen's head and each is willing to make deals to get it. Jorgen insists the Amber Hoard was a myth invented to explain ordinary plunder, but locals have noticed him making secret trips to sea caves north of the harbor. The truth is complicated: the Hoard was real, Jorgen did hide it, but he's been slowly distributing it to families of crew members who died under his command. He'll die before revealing its location to Thomlin, whom he holds responsible for a mutiny attempt that killed good sailors. Player may hear that strangers have been asking about the old fisherman who 'used to be somebody important,' and that Jorgen hasn't slept in his house for three nights.",
