        "difficultyTier": "beginner",
        "hiddenInfo": "The anchorage serves as neutral ground for a secret annual meeting between representatives of all major naval powers: Astraholm, the Zerathis Imperium, and the Lumeris Republic. Officially, these powers are rivals or enemies. Unofficially, their admirals recognized decades ago that piracy, sea monsters, and unknown threats require occasional cooperation. The meetings establish informal rules of engagement, share intelligence about common dangers, and quietly resolve disputes that might otherwise escalate to war. This year's meeting is threatened by a leak: someone has been selling information about the gatherings to the Astrael War-Cults, who view any form of peace cooperation as heresy against the god of conflict. War-Cult agents are planning to assassinate attendees from all three nations during the meeting, hoping to trigger a three-way naval war. The Free Sail Consortium, which facilitates the meetings while maintaining plausible deniability, has learned of the threat but cannot warn the admirals without exposing their own involvement. They're seeking outside agents who can neutralize the War-Cult threat without anyone official knowing why. Player may hear that merchant convoys have been advised to avoid the anchorage during a specific week, with no explanation given, and that Free Sail Consortium representatives are asking unusually probing questions about travelers' combat capabilities.",
