        "difficultyTier": "beginner",
        "hiddenInfo": "The fishing grounds have become contested territory in an unlikely conflict: three separate fishing cooperatives claim hereditary rights to the most productive waters, and their dispute has escalated from legal challenges to sabotage to violence. The Silverfin Collective insists their ancestors discovered the grounds; the Deepwater Brotherhood claims a century-old treaty grants them exclusive access; and the newcomer Sunrise Fleet argues that under Republican law, no one can own the ocean. The Border Wardens have been called to mediate, but their representativeWarden Tia Saltwindhas discovered that all three cooperatives are partially correct, and the original documents have been forged by an unknown party specifically to create this conflict. Someone wants the fishing grounds emptied of legitimate operations, and Tia suspects it's related to a sunken cargo ship she's found references to in old maritime recordsa ship carrying something valuable enough to kill for. The cooperatives are too invested in their conflict to listen to her theory, and Tia needs help investigating the wreck while keeping all three factions from murdering each other. Player may hear that fishing boats have been finding unusual debris in their netsworked metal and strange crystals that don't match anything from the known wreck registry.",
