        "hiddenInfo": "The waystation's isolation makes it perfect for activities that require privacy, and its current operators have transformed the repair facilities into a black-market modification shop for vessels. Smugglers, pirates, and legitimate merchants who need 'special features' come here to have hidden compartments installed, hull markings changed, and magitech systems modified to avoid detection. The operation is run by a brilliant but paranoid high goblin engineer named Wicket Brassknuckle, who maintains security through a simple policy: everyone who uses his services becomes complicit in everyone else's crimes, creating mutual blackmail that ensures silence. The system worked perfectly until last month, when a Zerathis Imperial inquisitor arrived seeking modifications to a personal vessel. The inquisitor, traveling incognito, wanted smuggling compartments installedbut Wicket recognized the hull design as Imperial Navy and realized he was dealing with either a traitor or a spy. Either way, the inquisitor's presence threatens to bring imperial attention to an operation that has so far avoided scrutiny from any major power. Wicket is considering whether to complete the job and hope for the best, kill the inquisitor and risk imperial investigation into the disappearance, or reach out to someone who can help him understand what he's actually dealing with. Player may hear that the waystation is offering unusually generous discounts on repairs, as if trying to attract visitors who might help with an unspecified problem.",
