        "difficultyTier": "intermediate",
        "hiddenInfo": "The patrol base has become an unlikely hub for a clandestine religious movement: the Tide Keepers, a faction within the Lunar Concordance that believes Luna's true teachings have been corrupted by political compromise with the crown. The base's chaplain, Father Morvyn Stillwater, has been converting sailors to this austere interpretation, which holds that true faith requires separation from worldly authority. The Tide Keepers haven't done anything illegal, but their growing influence concerns the Bastion Yards leadership, who see religious division within the navy as a security threat. Morvyn has been quietly transferred three times, but his following has only grown, and sailors seek assignment to wherever he's posted. The situation has attracted attention from an unexpected quarter: agents of the Radiant Assembly from Zerathis have begun making contact with disaffected Tide Keepers, suggesting that their dissatisfaction with Luna worship might indicate openness to 'purer' faiths. The Zerathis agents are essentially trying to recruit naval personnel as spies by appealing to their religious discontent. Father Morvyn has realized his movement is being targeted but isn't sure who to trust with this information. Player may hear that the base's chaplain has been holding services at unusual hours, drawing larger crowds each time, and that several sailors have requested transfers to follow him despite the career consequences.",
