        "difficultyTier": "expert",
        "hiddenInfo": "The platform's research team has made a discovery they're not allowed to publish: the boundary between navigable ocean and permanent ice is not natural. Deep-scan instruments have revealed a line of massive structures beneath the ice shelf, forming a barrier that appears to regulate temperature and current flow across the entire northern ocean. The structures are clearly Lunarian, and they're still functioningbarely. The research suggests that if these structures fail, the ice will begin advancing southward at an alarming rate, potentially rendering vast stretches of ocean impassable within a century. The Twilight Seekers, who fund the platform, have classified these findings and are desperately seeking a way to repair or stabilize the structures. But accessing them requires diving beneath the ice sheet itself, a feat that would kill any normal person within minutes. They need someone or something capable of surviving in conditions that would freeze blood solid, and they're willing to pay almost any price. Player may hear that the platform has posted job listings for 'extreme environment specialists' with unusual requirements including 'resistance to magical cold' and 'experience with precursor technology.",
