        "difficultyTier": "advanced",
        "hiddenInfo": "The station was established five years ago to study acoustic anomalies detected by imperial naval vessels rhythmic pulses from the abyssal depths that followed mathematical patterns too complex for natural phenomena. Using experimental magitech hydrophones, researchers have mapped the signals to a specific location: a trench seventeen thousand feet below the surface where something is broadcasting a repeating message. Lead researcher Caelum Voss has devoted his career to decoding the transmission, and last month he achieved a breakthrough the signals aren't random noise but a coordinate system, updated weekly, tracking something that moves through the deep ocean on predictable routes. Voss believes an intelligent species lives in the abyss, one that has been navigating the deeps since before humans built boats. He's requested funding for a deep-diving bell to make contact, but his petition was rejected by nervous admirals who fear what first contact might mean for imperial naval supremacy. Voss has begun seeking private funding, and rumors of his discovery have attracted attention from the Twilight Seekers, who've dispatched an agent to either recruit him or ensure his research doesn't fall into the wrong hands. Meanwhile, the signals have changed for the first time in five years, they've stopped their regular pattern and begun broadcasting what Voss believes is a response to the station's own transmissions.",
