        "difficultyTier": "advanced",
        "hiddenInfo": "Observers report mist-wreathed islands appearing on no chart, where ruins of unknown origin rise from fog-shrouded shores. Ships attempting to approach find themselves turned away by currents that have will and purposethe islands are protected by Lunarian navigation-denial systems designed to hide a prison complex where the precursors contained entities too dangerous to destroy. Lieutenant Vera Ironside has become obsessed with reaching the islands after glimpsing a child waving from the shore. The child is realshipwreck survivors pushed toward the islands by the same currents that prevent approach have been trapped there for generations, their descendants born into imprisonment, unable to leave or signal for help beyond simple waving. Vera's requests for investigation have been denied by superiors who dismiss the sightings. She is planning an unauthorized expedition using modified equipment she has designed to counter the deflecting currents. Her crew is dividedsome believe her, others think she has lost her mind, and a few are reporting her behavior to headquarters. The islands hold both the trapped survivor community and the prison complex the Lunarians built. Precursors imprisoned some kind of eldritch being that they couldn't catalogue, destroy nor communicate that remains contained (or it just stays there because it wants) but aware, and it has been influencing the survivors for generations. Reaching the islands means confronting both a rescue mission and an ancient threat. Player may hear that the station commander has been acting strangely, spending hours staring west through her spyglass, and that she has been requisitioning unusual navigation equipment without proper authorization.",
