        "difficultyTier": "advanced",
        "hiddenInfo": "The ice's unusual stability stems from geothermal patterns generated by ancient Lunarian climate-control systems still functioning belowpart of a network that kept research facilities habitable in extreme environments. Clan elders forbid investigating warm spots beneath the ice because hunters who descended found stasis chambers containing Lunarian researchers who never woke when their civilization fell. A young hunter named Kira Frostheart descended into a melt hole and returned speaking in fragments about 'the sleeping ones below.' She brought back a device that projects images of this location before the ice existed, showing a thriving research complex studying the polar magnetic field. The elders want to destroy the device and exile Kira because they fear the Frost Covenant will claim the site and transform their sacred grounds into an excavation. Kira wants to return because she saw indicators showing some chambers still hold living occupants in stable stasispeople waiting to be rescued. A Frost Covenant agent posing as a trader has already noticed the disturbance and is gathering information. Players can help by mediating between Kira and the elders, offering protection against Covenant exploitation. They can descend with Kira to properly assess the facility, attempt to revive a Lunarian, or help the clan negotiate with outside powers from a position of knowledge rather than ignorance. The Frost Covenant agent must be identified before they report the discovery. Player may hear that a hunter returned from the forbidden warm spots 'touched by spirits' and that the clan council has been meeting in emergency sessions about whether to exile her.",
