        "hiddenInfo": "Fishermen have pulled up Lunarian artifacts in their netsmetal objects that don't corrode, crystals that glow faintly, and fragments of machinery whose purpose defies identification. The concentration marks a debris field on the seabed from a Lunarian vessel that crash-landed during the Fall while carrying evacuees to safety. Three weeks ago, a fishing crew hauled up a sealed stasis pod containing a Lunarian in perfect preservationa historian named Renne who was evacuating. The terrified crew sold the pod to Convergence Exchange factor Bellamy Ironquill, who has been secretly auctioning it. Both the Veiled Archive and the Sunbound Continuum have sent representatives. The pod's preservation systems are failing because the pod was designed to open upon reaching a destination that no longer exists; condensation has begun forming inside, and Selen will die within days if nothing changes. Players can intervene by outbidding the factions to control what happens to Selen, helping the Veiled Archive secure the pod for careful study, sabotaging the Continuum's acquisition to prevent military exploitation, or finding a way to repair the stasis systems. If the pod opens and Renne survives, she becomes an invaluable source of precursor knowledgebut she will need help processing that her civilization is gone. Player may hear that Bellamy Ironquill has been buying rounds at the dockside tavern celebrating some secret windfall, and that strange folk in expensive clothes have been arriving asking about 'unusual salvage.",
