        "difficultyTier": "advanced",
        "hiddenInfo": "The research station's permanent ice samples have revealed something impossible: organic material frozen in the deepest cores that doesn't match any known species. The organisms appear to be engineered rather than evolved, with cellular structures suggesting they were designed to survive conditions that would kill anything natural. The Twilight Seekers believe these are remnants of Lunarian bioengineering projects, organisms created for purposes that can only be guessed at. More troubling, some samples have shown signs of cellular activity when exposed to certain mana frequenciesas if the organisms aren't dead, merely dormant. The station's lead researcher has sealed the most reactive samples in special containment and is debating whether to attempt controlled reanimation or destroy the samples before something goes wrong. She's seeking consultation from experts in Lunarian biology, but trusting the wrong person could result in either the research being stolen or the samples being declared too dangerous to study. Player may hear that the survey point has been requesting specialized biological containment equipment and that one researcher was evacuated with 'frostbite of unusual character",
