        "difficultyTier": "intermediate",
        "hiddenInfo": "The geothermal station has tapped into more than hot waterits deep bore has punctured a Lunarian facility that appears to have been a biological research laboratory. Samples from the bore water contain genetic material from species that don't exist in any modern record, including what may be early prototypes of the Voidfangs. The station's engineers have been quietly selling samples to interested parties, recognizing the scientific value but underestimating the danger. Among their customers is a Zerathis bioweapon researcher who has been attempting to culture the organisms, with results that have already required the quiet disposal of several test subjects. The researcher needs more samples and has offered to purchase the entire station's output, but the engineers are getting nervous about their customer's escalating demands. Meanwhile, something in the deep bore has begun risingcreatures or constructs that emerged from the punctured facility and have been killing workers who venture too close to the drilling site. The station is facing a crisis it can't explain to authorities without revealing illegal activities. Player may hear that the geothermal station has experienced unusual worker turnover and that bodies have been cremated rather than returned to families, attributed to 'volcanic accidents.",
