        "difficultyTier": "intermediate",
        "hiddenInfo": "Captain William Driftwood is either a brilliant navigator or the most audacious con artist on the southern seas. He claims to have mapped a safe passage through the Shattered Straits a route that would cut three weeks off voyages to the far western markets and make whoever controls it fantastically wealthy. He's selling shares in an expedition to establish the route, and merchants are lining up despite the obvious risks. The problem is that the last four captains who claimed to know the passage all disappeared, and William was the first mate on two of those voyages. His former partner, a navigator named Yara Saltwind, has been spreading warnings that Marcus murdered the captains and stole their charts but she's also been buying shares through intermediaries, suggesting she believes the route is real. The Merchant Marine has dispatched agents to either verify William's claims or expose his fraud before investors lose fortunes. William himself seems genuinely confident, but he's also increasingly paranoid, carrying weapons openly and sleeping on his ship rather than in the anchorage. Someone is following him, and it might not be Yara. Player may hear that Captain Driftwood is recruiting crew for a 'guaranteed fortune' and that three people who met with him privately have since left the anchorage in a hurry.",
