        "difficultyTier": "intermediate",
        "hiddenInfo": "The crossroads serves as neutral ground for negotiations between powers that can't be seen meeting publiclyand this season has drawn participants for a gathering that could reshape continental politics. Representatives from all major nations have converged to discuss a proposal from the Free Sail Consortium: a mutual defense treaty against non-human threats, specifically creatures emerging from the deep ocean with increasing frequency. The treaty would require unprecedented cooperation between enemies, and negotiations have nearly collapsed several times. The Astrael War-Cults have sent agents to sabotage the talks, viewing any peace cooperation as heresy. The Radiant Assembly wants the treaty but only if Zerathis leads the coalition. Lumeris refuses any agreement that doesn't include provisions against slavery. Astraholm suspects the entire proposal is a Free Sail Consortium power grab. Into this mess has walked an unexpected participant: a representative of the merfolk kingdoms, offering alliance against the deep-sea threats in exchange for recognition of underwater territorial rights. Player may hear that ships approaching the crossroads have been turned away by heavily armed escorts and that the Consortium has warned all traffic to avoid the area until further notice.",
