        "difficultyTier": "intermediate",
        "hiddenInfo": "Lighthouse keeper Ruth Gainsborough has discovered a pattern that no one wants to acknowledge: over the past five years, ships responding to distress signals from the eastern shoals have a forty percent chance of wrecking themselves, and a specific salvage compan Rothwell & Sons Maritime Recover always arrives first to 'recover' the cargo. Ruth believes the lighthouse's previous keeper, old Brennan Coalhurst, was complicit in a wrecking scheme, using the lighthouse signals to lure rescue ships onto the rocks. When Brennan died last year, she found coded logbooks suggesting he received payments for decades. But when she reported her findings, the harbormaster dismissed her as paranoid, the local magistrate lost her evidence, and Brennan's grieving family threatened to sue her for defamation. Now she's noticed the signals being altered at night someone else has access to the lighthouse and is continuing the scheme. Her assistant, a quiet young man named Thomlin, was hired by the harbor authority over her objections, and she's begun to suspect he's the one changing the signals. She needs outsiders to help her catch the operation in the act before another ship goes down. Player may hear that the new lighthouse keeper has been making accusations against a respected local family and that ships have been having unusual trouble in waters that should be well-charted.",
