        "difficultyTier": "intermediate",
        "hiddenInfo": "The settlement is currently consumed by the upcoming chieftain election to replace the aging Hakon Whitehowl, who has announced his retirement after two decades of leadership. The contest has become a bitter rivalry between his children: Kara Whitehowl, who advocates for magitech adoption and modernization, and Eirik Whitehowl, who champions traditional ways and views innovation as corruption. The election will be decided through a series of trials demonstrating leadership, combat prowess, and ability to solve clan problemsbut both siblings are desperately seeking outside help to gain advantage. Kara wants allies who can demonstrate magitech's practical value in protecting the settlement, while Eirik seeks those who can prove traditional methods still work against modern threats. The entire settlement is divided between progressive and traditionalist factions, with families split and old friendships strained. Visiting players will likely be approached by both siblings, each offering rewards and alliance in exchange for help winning specific trials or swaying public opinion. The outcome will determine not just leadership but Skjoldheim's entire future directionwhether Frostrend embraces the magitech revolution or doubles down on the survival methods that sustained them through the Long Winter.",
