        "hiddenInfo": "The agricultural heart of the Empire faces a crisis that could starve millions: a blight is spreading through the grain fields, resistant to every treatment agricultural mages have attempted. The Radiant Assembly has declared the blight divine punishment for insufficient devotion, demanding increased tithes and public penance. House Varnex, which controls the grain trade, has begun hoarding supplies to profit from the coming shortage. Imperial Administration has been suppressing news of the blight's extent, fearing panic, but the truth is becoming impossible to hide. A young agricultural researcher named Elena Goldfield has discovered something the authorities don't want known: the blight isn't natural. Its spread pattern suggests deliberate introduction, and trace elements in affected crops match compounds produced only by advanced magitech processes. Someone engineered this plague and released it intentionally. Elena's attempts to report her findings have been ignored or actively suppressed, and she's begun to fear for her safety. She needs help getting her evidence to someone who can act on itand identifying who would benefit from starving the Empire's heartland. The list of suspects with both motive and capability is disturbingly short, and it includes factions within the imperial government itself. Player may hear that grain prices have been rising steadily and that farmers in affected regions have been forbidden from discussing crop conditions with outsiders",
