        "hiddenInfo": "The capital of Astraholm faces a succession crisis that the Crownward Compact was designed to prevent. King Aldric has two heirs: his daughter Liara, trained in diplomacy and administration, and his son Roderic, a military commander beloved by House Valemor. The Compact technically favors Liara as the elder, but Roderic has been building support among nobles who believe Astraholm needs strong military leadership rather than careful management. Neither heir is evil or incompetenteach genuinely believes they would serve Astraholm betterbut their supporters have begun maneuvering in ways that threaten to tear the kingdom apart. House Valemor supports Roderic; House Hadrick backs Liara; House Stoneveil has tried to remain neutral but is being pressured from both sides. The Lunar Concordance, bound by religious neutrality, cannot officially intervene but has been working behind the scenes to prevent open conflict. Into this powder keg has come a troubling discovery: someone has been forging documents that make each faction believe the other is planning a coup. The forgeries are expert quality, designed to escalate tensions to the breaking point. High Oracle Maelis Dawnveil has identified the forgeries but cannot determine their source, and she fears that revealing them without knowing the forger's identity will only generate accusations rather than resolution. She needs discreet investigators who can trace the documents' origin before Astraholm's stability collapses. Player may hear that noble houses have been recalling soldiers from frontier postings and that the Night Archives has been unusually active in the capital's shadows.",
