        "hiddenInfo": "The naval port's shipyards have become the site of a competition that could determine Astraholm's future defensive capabilities. The Bastion Yards are developing a new warship class incorporating magitech systems far more advanced than anything in current servicebut the project is behind schedule, over budget, and plagued by sabotage. Three prototype vessels have suffered mysterious accidents that delayed construction by months each time. Master-Forgewright Dorian Kessel has been investigating and has identified a pattern: the sabotage specifically targets systems that would give Astraholm naval superiority over potential enemies. He suspects foreign involvementeither Zerathis preventing Astraholm from challenging their sea power, or Republican interests maintaining the current balance. But he can't prove which, and his investigations have been hampered by a lack of counterintelligence resources. The Astraholm Navy has no dedicated spy-catching capability; they've never needed one. Kessel needs someone who can identify the saboteurs before the project is canceled due to 'insurmountable technical difficulties.' The stakes go beyond this single ship class: if foreign agents can operate freely in Astraholm's most secure facilities, no defense project is safe. Player may hear that the Bastion Yards have implemented unprecedented security measures and that several skilled workers have been quietly dismissed without explanation.",
