        "hiddenInfo": "Grakhold is home to SC Dinas, a green orc football club with a century-long rivalry against FC Itlldo from the neighboring village of Skullkick. Their goalkeeper, a massive orc named Brogmar Ironpalm, has gone missing three days before the annual Great Derby match. The entire village has fallen into despair, convinced their rivals have kidnapped him or that dark omens have claimed their champion. In truth, Brogmar got catastrophically drunk celebrating his birthday behind the Team Quarters, stumbled to relieve himself near the latrine pit, passed out face-down in a ditch, and died of exposure and alcohol poisoning. His body lies hidden in tall weeds just twenty meters from his own bed, bloated and undiscovered because no orc wants to venture near the stinking latrine area. The village has sent search parties to distant locations, accused FC Itlldo of foul play, and consulted shamans about cursesall while the answer lies literally in their backyard. Players investigating the disappearance may notice flies buzzing near the Team Quarters, catch a peculiar smell distinct from the latrine, or simply think to check the obvious nearby areas the panicked orcs overlooked. The orcs are currently drinking themselves into deeper depression, alternating between weeping about their doomed season and threatening violence against Skullkick. If Brogmar's body is found, the village will need to face the embarrassing truth and find a replacement goalkeeper before the match.",
