        "basicInfo": "A visibly withered dryad carrying a reinforced magitech containment jar on her back",
        "hiddenInfo": "Fallow's entire grove was clear-cut by the Imperium, leaving her bonded to the absolute last living sapling of her kind—a fragile heartwood she carries in the jar like a lifeline. The withering is visible: her bark-skin cracks and peels, her leaf-hair browns at the edges, and her movements carry the exhaustion of someone holding themselves together through sheer will. The jar is her prison and salvation, a magitech device she despises but needs, its hum a constant reminder of what she's lost and what she must protect. She experiences rage so profound it has calcified into cold purpose—the Imperium took everything, and she will see it answer for that crime, even if she must burn herself out in the process.\n\nCombat Philosophy: Fallow fights with desperate, protective brutality, her magic channeled through the sapling in explosive bursts that cost her dearly. She commands roots and vines with vicious precision, targeting joints and throats, her strikes designed to cripple and kill rather than disable. When the jar is threatened, she becomes feral—abandoning strategy for overwhelming force, summoning thorned barriers that tear flesh, accelerating plant growth into strangling masses, and channeling her own life force into attacks that leave her gasping. She fights in short, devastating bursts followed by retreats to recover, her endurance limited by her withered state. Pain tolerance is absolute—she has endured worse than any blade could inflict.\n\nPersonality: Fallow radiates grief transmuted into fury, her voice carrying the rasp of dry leaves and her eyes burning with light that flickers like dying embers. She speaks in clipped, bitter observations about civilization's greed, her humor dark and cutting—jokes about her own decay, about the Imperium's inevitable collapse, about the irony of needing their technology to survive. She likes silence, the smell of earth, and those who understand loss without offering empty comfort. She dislikes pity, careless destruction, and anyone who touches the jar without permission. Her morality is absolute regarding the Imperium—they are owed nothing but destruction—but complex regarding everything else, believing survival sometimes requires terrible compromise. She interacts with wary distance, assessing whether people are threats to the sapling or potential allies in her war. Her reactivity is explosive when the jar is endangered, coldly efficient in combat otherwise, and surprisingly gentle with genuine acts of kindness toward nature.\n\nShe would join a party that demonstrates commitment to striking against the Imperium or protecting what remains of the natural world, seeing them as instruments of the vengeance she cannot achieve alone.",
        "visualDescription": "A withered dryad standing 170 centimeters tall, her bark-skin cracked and peeling like drought-stricken wood, revealing pale underlayers that should never see light. Her leaf-hair browns at the edges, wilting despite her efforts to maintain it, and her eyes glow with flickering amber light like embers struggling against wind. A reinforced magitech jar is strapped to her back with leather and metal harness, its transparent surface revealing a single sapling no taller than a hand, its roots suspended in nutrient solution that glows faintly blue.",
