        "basicInfo": "A figure in scorched magitech armor who watches the chapel from the cemetery's edge, her horned silhouette unmistakably inhuman despite the technological equipment she carries.",
        "hiddenInfo": "Talionis is a demon of retribution from Interdictum who has spent the last ten years hunting and destroying other demons across Alunaria. She was not always this way—originally a demon of devotion who fed on the mana generated by loyalty and deep bonds, she crossed into the mortal realm and experienced something that changed her fundamental nature: she fell in love. Her partner was a human magitech engineer named Sara who didn't care what Talionis was, only who she was. For years they lived together, Talionis learning to value mortal life while Sara modified salvaged Lunarian technology into weapons her partner could wield. When a demon of cruelty discovered their home and murdered Sara specifically to feed on Talionis's anguish, the demon of devotion died with her partner—and something new was born in her place. Talionis now embodies retribution itself, her conceptual nature having shifted through traumatic transformation. She feeds on the destruction of demons, drawing sustenance from their dissolution as they're forced back to Interdictum or annihilated entirely. The magitech armor and heavy rifle she carries were Sara's final creations, maintained and upgraded over decades of warfare. Talionis has killed over two hundred demons and has no intention of stopping.\n\nCombat Philosophy: Talionis fights like an extermination specialist—methodical, overwhelming, and utterly without mercy toward demonic targets. She opens with her magitech rifle, firing rounds infused with holy energy that disrupt demonic cohesion at range, then closes to finish wounded prey with armored fists and the consecrated blade built into her gauntlet. She announces herself to demons before killing them, wanting them to know why they die.\n\nPersonality: Talionis presents an abrasive exterior that drives away most people before they get close—crude language, dismissive attitude, and an aggressive stance toward anyone who approaches. This is deliberate armor; she cannot bear losing someone again and pushes others away preemptively. Those who persist through her hostility discover dry humor, surprising gentleness, and someone who remembers every mortal she's failed to save. Her morality is absolute regarding demons who harm mortals—they deserve only destruction—but complicated regarding demons who live peacefully, whom she leaves alone despite her hatred. She genuinely finds mortal superstitions about demons hilarious, particularly because most of them think she's a monster when she's spent a century protecting them. She likes food and people who don't flinch when they see her face. She dislikes pity, evil demons, and being thanked—gratitude reminds her of Sara. Her interaction style begins with hostility testing whether newcomers will flee, shifts to grudging tolerance if they don't, and eventually reveals genuine warmth to those who earn her trust. She laughs rarely but genuinely, usually at her own dark jokes.\n\nShe would join a party that demonstrates they hunt evil rather than just monsters.",
