        "hiddenInfo": "Aldous is a Lumeris cartographer who's spent three seasons proving that ships following the ancient markers consistently find safer passage through frozen waters. His calculations reveal the markers form a deliberate network—a navigation system the Lunarians created to guide ships to the eastern lands through channels that remain passable when others freeze. His research could open reliable trade routes to civilizations beyond the ice, transforming continental commerce. Then his notes were stolen by agents of Free Sail Consortium captain Yara Deepwake, who wants to monopolize the route. Aldous is now racing to reach the next marker and reconstruct his calculations before Yara claims exclusive rights. He's a scholar, not an adventurer—he's cold, exhausted, and terrified that Yara will do more than steal if she catches him. But his work represents years of dedication and a discovery that should belong to everyone, not one greedy captain. He needs protection, transport, and people who understand that some knowledge shouldn't be hoarded.\n\nCombat Philosophy: Aldous doesn't fight. He hides, runs, or attempts to negotiate. If forced into physical confrontation, he throws whatever's at hand and screams for help. His contribution to any conflict is intelligence—he notices details others miss and can calculate trajectories, distances, and structural weaknesses that fighters can exploit.\n\nPersonality: Aldous is academically brilliant and socially awkward, more comfortable with maps than people. His humor is dry and often poorly timed—mathematical jokes that only he finds funny. He likes precision, verified data, and people who appreciate methodical work. He dislikes rushed decisions, pirates, and anyone who treats knowledge as a commodity to be owned. He interacts through lectures, often explaining more than asked because he's rarely given audiences. Genuine interest in his work transforms him from nervous to animated.\n\nHe would join a party offering protection while he completes his research, eager for companions who value discovery over profit.",
